52
00:08:56,760 --> 00:08:58,760
Wolfgang...

53
00:08:58,920 --> 00:09:02,549
Amadeus Mozart.

54
00:09:04,280 --> 00:09:08,105
The man you accuse yourself of killing.

55
00:09:10,560 --> 00:09:12,596
You've heard that?

56
00:09:12,840 --> 00:09:14,840
Is it true?

57
00:09:23,120 --> 00:09:25,953
For God's sake, my son...

58
00:09:28,000 --> 00:09:32,596
if you have something to confess,
do it now.

59
00:09:33,000 --> 00:09:35,720
Give yourself some peace.

60
00:09:39,160 --> 00:09:41,160
He...

61
00:09:42,400 --> 00:09:44,400
was my idol.

62
00:09:47,080 --> 00:09:49,230
Mozart.

63
00:09:50,200 --> 00:09:53,940
I can't think of a time
when I didn't know his name.

64
00:09:54,040 --> 00:09:55,860
I was playing childish games,

65
00:09:55,960 --> 00:10:00,180
when he was playing music
for kings and emperors.

66
00:10:00,280 --> 00:10:02,840
Even the pope in Rome.

67
00:10:06,600 --> 00:10:08,795
I admit, I was jealous,

68
00:10:09,120 --> 00:10:12,300
when I heard the tales they told about him.

69
00:10:12,400 --> 00:10:14,780
None of the brilliant little prodigy,

70
00:10:14,880 --> 00:10:19,556
but of his father,
who had taught him everything.

71
00:10:19,760 --> 00:10:22,991
My father, he did not care for music.

72
00:10:23,640 --> 00:10:25,100
When I told him,

73
00:10:25,200 --> 00:10:28,685
how I wished I could be like Mozart,

74
00:10:28,800 --> 00:10:33,140
he would say, 
"Why? Do you want to be a trained monkey?

75
00:10:33,240 --> 00:10:39,020
You'd like me to drag you around Europe,
doing tricks like a circus freak?".

76
00:10:41,680 --> 00:10:43,900
How could I tell him

77
00:10:44,000 --> 00:10:48,250
what music meant to me?

78
00:11:01,120 --> 00:11:04,300
While my father prayed earnestly to God,

79
00:11:04,400 --> 00:11:06,960
to protect commerce,

80
00:11:07,400 --> 00:11:09,400
I would offer up,

81
00:11:09,440 --> 00:11:11,510
secretly...

82
00:11:12,000 --> 00:11:15,220
the proudest prayer a boy could think of.

83
00:11:15,320 --> 00:11:19,438
"Lord, make me a great composer.

84
00:11:19,680 --> 00:11:23,468
Let me celebrate your glory through music,

85
00:11:23,680 --> 00:11:26,353
and be celebrated myself.

86
00:11:27,720 --> 00:11:30,420
Make me famous through the world, 
dear God.

87
00:11:30,520 --> 00:11:33,080
Make me immortal.

88
00:11:33,840 --> 00:11:35,840
After I die...

89
00:11:35,920 --> 00:11:41,700
let people speak my name forever
with love for what I wrote.

90
00:11:41,840 --> 00:11:43,840
In return...

91
00:11:44,520 --> 00:11:47,920
I will give you my chastity...

92
00:11:48,000 --> 00:11:50,230
my industry...

93
00:11:52,120 --> 00:11:57,300
my deepest humility,
every hour of my life.

94
00:11:57,400 --> 00:11:59,400
Amen".

95
00:12:00,440 --> 00:12:02,990
And do you know what happened?

96
00:12:03,120 --> 00:12:05,120
A miracle.

97
00:12:21,840 --> 00:12:24,798
My life changed forever.

98
00:12:25,640 --> 00:12:29,220
Of course I knew God had arranged it all.
That was obvious.

99
00:12:29,320 --> 00:12:34,500
One minute I was a frustrated boy
in an obscure little town.

100
00:12:34,600 --> 00:12:36,420
The next I was here...

101
00:12:36,520 --> 00:12:40,005
in Vienna, city of musicians...

102
00:12:40,600 --> 00:12:44,195
and Emperor Joseph, the musical king.

103
00:12:44,400 --> 00:12:49,260
In a few years, I was his court composer. 
Isn't that incredible?

104
00:12:49,360 --> 00:12:52,580
Night after night I sat right next
to the emperor of Austria

105
00:12:52,680 --> 00:12:54,540
playing duets with him,

106
00:12:54,640 --> 00:12:57,870
correcting the royal sight-reading.

107
00:13:00,440 --> 00:13:04,095
Actually, the man had no ear at all.

108
00:13:04,440 --> 00:13:07,245
But what did it matter?

109
00:13:07,280 --> 00:13:10,431
He adored my music.

110
00:13:11,200 --> 00:13:13,200
Tell me.

111
00:13:13,240 --> 00:13:15,620
If you had been me,

112
00:13:16,120 --> 00:13:20,965
wouldn't you have thought
God had accepted your vow?

113
00:13:22,160 --> 00:13:24,740
And believe me, I honored it.

114
00:13:24,840 --> 00:13:27,340
I was a model of virtue.

115
00:13:27,440 --> 00:13:29,740
I kept my hands off women.

116
00:13:29,840 --> 00:13:34,220
I worked hours every day teaching students, 
many of them for free.

117
00:13:34,320 --> 00:13:39,420
Sitting on endless committees
to help poor musicians.

118
00:13:39,520 --> 00:13:42,140
Work and work and work, 
that was all my life.

119
00:13:42,240 --> 00:13:44,276
And it was wonderful.

120
00:13:44,520 --> 00:13:46,875
Everybody liked me.

121
00:13:48,840 --> 00:13:50,910
I liked myself.

122
00:13:53,720 --> 00:13:56,280
Until he came.

123
00:13:58,160 --> 00:14:03,340
He came to Vienna to play
some of his music,

124
00:14:03,440 --> 00:14:08,798
at the residence of his employer,
the Prince Archbishop of Salzburg.

125
00:14:10,040 --> 00:14:13,271
Eagerly, I went there to seek him out.

126
00:14:16,160 --> 00:14:18,276
That night...

127
00:14:19,960 --> 00:14:22,155
changed my life.

128
00:14:26,480 --> 00:14:28,860
As I wandered through the salon,

129
00:14:28,960 --> 00:14:31,660
I played a little game with myself.

130
00:14:31,760 --> 00:14:36,100
This man had written
his first concerto at the age of 4,

131
00:14:36,200 --> 00:14:40,955
his first symphony at 7,
a full-scale opera at 12.

132
00:14:41,360 --> 00:14:43,510
Did it show?

133
00:14:45,160 --> 00:14:47,720
Is talent like that

134
00:14:47,920 --> 00:14:50,593
written on the face?

135
00:14:51,920 --> 00:14:54,354
Which one of them

136
00:14:55,160 --> 00:14:58,152
could he be?

137
00:16:55,720 --> 00:16:58,109
Mozart is not here.

138
00:17:03,160 --> 00:17:04,460
- Stop it.
- I`am.

139
00:17:04,560 --> 00:17:06,940
- Stop it.
- I`am stopping it.

140
00:17:07,040 --> 00:17:10,953
I`am. I'm stopping it. Slowly.

141
00:17:11,160 --> 00:17:15,438
There. You see? I've stopped.

142
00:17:15,640 --> 00:17:17,660
- Now we're going back.
- No.

143
00:17:17,760 --> 00:17:20,420
Yes, yes.
Listen, you don't know where you are.

144
00:17:20,520 --> 00:17:23,240
Here, everything goes backwards.

145
00:17:23,480 --> 00:17:28,076
People walk backwards, and dance backwards, 
and sing backwards and even talk backwards.

146
00:17:28,680 --> 00:17:32,930
- That's stupid.
- Why? People fart backwards.

147
00:17:34,840 --> 00:17:36,840
Ssa-ym-ssik.

148
00:17:37,080 --> 00:17:38,740
Ssa-ym-ssik.

149
00:17:38,840 --> 00:17:41,220
Yes, you are. You are very sick.

150
00:17:41,320 --> 00:17:44,596
No. Say it backwards, shitwit.

151
00:17:45,160 --> 00:17:47,160
Ssa-ym-ssik.

152
00:17:47,560 --> 00:17:49,560
Ssik, kiss.

153
00:17:49,640 --> 00:17:52,029
Ym, my. Ssa.

154
